The paper deals with optimization methods for machine learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of stochastic gradients and Gaussian processes suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most likely category. The paper also uses Bayesian optimization, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and the probabilistic line search algorithm could be applied to neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes experiments on image classification (cs.CV), which is another application of machine learning.
